# Architecture And Modularization Guardrails

- Before coding, define boundaries: feature scope, data contract, and module ownership.
- Frontend rules:
  - Keep page/container components focused on orchestration.
  - Extract reusable UI and state logic into dedicated components/hooks/modules.
  - Avoid adding unrelated logic into a single large file.
- Backend rules:
  - Keep transport/router code separate from domain logic and storage details.
  - Prefer dedicated modules per business capability (e.g. employee, tools, workspace).
  - Keep handlers thin; move validation/IO logic to feature modules/services.
- For new features, prefer extending existing module patterns instead of ad-hoc code.
- If a file grows too complex, split immediately during implementation rather than postponing.
